Aluminum Stockpiles in Japan Gain for First Month in Four

-- B y   A y a   T a k a d a
-- 
2011-05-16T01:43:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/aluminum-stockpiles-in-japan-gain-for-first-month-in-four-1-.html
Aluminum stockpiles in  Japan 
increased 8.9 percent in April from a month earlier, the first
gain in four months, after the March 11 earthquake and tsunami
disrupted auto manufacturing and reduced shipments.  Inventories held in Yokohama, Nagoya and Osaka ports
expanded to 219,100 metric tons at the end of April from 201,200
tons as of March 31, trading company  Marubeni Corp. (8002)  said today
by e-mail. The volume is the largest since January, when
inventories reached 220,700 tons, according to Marubeni, the
largest Japanese importer of the metal used in cars and houses.  A breakdown of Japanese stockpiles data follows:  To contact the reporters on this story:
